		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.79]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Been out of touch for a bit so I am just catching up - <br /> <br />CHA has NOTHING to do with charm/mezz.&nbsp;&nbsp;This was discussed in a forum at a SoE hosted EQ convention a couple of years ago.  At this convention the developer revealed that CHA has no effect on charm or mezz.  Not duration. Not resistance. Nothing.  What they did state was that if you try to lull a mob (Kelin's Lugubrious Lament for example) and the mob resists there is a chance (a second check) that the mob will ignore you or aggro you.  That 2nd check IS influenced by CHA.  So, CHA reduces the chance of a critical failure on lull songs.  If you pull for your group this is a rather useful thing to know.</p>
