<p>I always worked to increase my cha to it's maximum value.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am convinced it helped me a great deal.  Being able to lull and pull without aggroing mobs on resists is a huge advantage...especially in the levels before you can use Fading Memories to start over.   <br /> <br />In addition I alwasy made sure I was chabuffed to further reduce aggro chances.   I got a reputation as a very good bard because I very seldom created trains.  I was able to pull groups above my level and therefore level quickly. <br /> <br />When I leveled and bagan collecting aa's I put them into the abilities that increased the power of my songs and worked on raising level caps and such.  Singing Mastery, Instrument Mastery, Jamfest, Anonyes Tutalage, and Echo of Telosia.  I still maintain Max Cha when I pull.   I now can pull all-65 hard ldons in much the same way I used to pull easy ones....lulling and pulling.   If I hit an extremely resistant mob that I cannot lull, he will just stand there and not come after me.  If he resists say three times I will Fade Pull.   Being able to lull many of the mobs allows me to save mana for fading the resistant ones so I never have to med.  As a result I can pull a hard ldon as fast and safely as I can pull an easy one. <br /> <br />Cha isn't solely responsible for me being to pull this way but it is a huge part of it.</p>
